pageTitle: Australia Four Nations train-on squad announce additions » League Unlimited
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {18076=The Australian Rugby League today announced that the following players have been added to the Australian VB Kangaroos Four Nations' Train-on squad:   Jason King - Manly Sea Eagles Brent Kite - Manly Sea Eagles Jamie Lyon - Manly Sea Eagles Anthony Watmough - Manly Sea Eagles Brent Tate - Warriors     Australian VB Kangaroos Four Nations Train-on squad as of 13/09/2010 Brisbane Broncos: Darren Lockyer, Sam Thaiday. Canterbury-Bankstown Bulldogs: Michael Ennis, Ben Hannant, Jamal Idris, Josh Morris Cronulla Sharks: Paul Gallen Melbourne Storm: Cooper Cronk, Greg Inglis, Billy Slater, Cameron Smith Newcastle Knights: Kurt Gidley North Queensland Cowboys: Matt Scott, Johnathan Thurston, Willie Tonga Parramatta Eels: Jarryd Hayne, Timana Tahu South Sydney Rabbitohs: David Taylor Manly Sea Eagles: Jason King, Brent Kite, Jamie Lyon, Anthony Watmough Warriors: Brent Tate   The train-on squad will assemble at Redfern Oval at 10.30am on Wednesday, 15 September, 2010.   Please note that players selected in the Prime Minister's XIII squad (to be announced later today) will also be eligible for inclusion in the VB Kangaroos squad to contest the 2010 Four Nations.}
